BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 688 Td (it forms tall clouds called cumulonimbus clouds. Inside these clouds,) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 673 Td (water droplets and ice crash together, creating static electricity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 658 Td (When enough electricity builds up, it releases as lightning. The) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 643 Td (lightning heats the air so fast that it expands and creates a loud) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 628 Td (boom we call thunder. Light travels faster than sound, so we always) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 613 Td (see lightning before we hear thunder.) Tj ET
